; Regression test for issue #2945: aux_date vs date in --effective mode.
;
; When --effective is used, item_t::use_aux_date must NOT be set during
; journal parsing.  If it is, then date() returns the aux_date during
; automated transaction evaluation, making "aux_date != date" always
; false — which breaks assertions and predicates that distinguish the
; two dates.  The global use_aux_date flag should only take effect at
; report time, not during parsing.

= expr "cleared and aux_date"
    assert aux_date != date

2018/12/31=2028/11/01 * Test
    Expenses:Foo     $100
    Assets:Checking

test bal --effective
               $-100  Assets:Checking
                $100  Expenses:Foo
--------------------
                   0
end test
